# basic-infra shared Redis ACL file (ADR-0014).
#
# TEMPLATE ONLY — do NOT cp this directly to users.acl. Redis' aclfile parser
# REJECTS `#` comment lines ("should start with user keyword"), so the live file
# must contain ONLY `user ...` lines. Generate it with `make redis-acl-bootstrap`,
# which substitutes the admin password AND strips these comment/blank lines.
#
# Set a strong admin password before first start and keep the live file out of
# public sharing (it is git-ignored). The control plane (redis_shared.cli) appends
# per-tenant `app_<namespace>` users here via ACL SETUSER + ACL SAVE.
#
# `default` is disabled so every connection must authenticate as a named user.
# `admin` is the control-plane account; BASIC_INFRA_REDIS_ADMIN_USERNAME=admin
# and BASIC_INFRA_REDIS_ADMIN_PASSWORD must match the password set below.

user default off

user admin on >REPLACE_WITH_STRONG_ADMIN_PASSWORD ~* &* +@all
